HEADWORD: Conirostres
<hw>Co`ni*ros"tres</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>conus</ets> cone + <ets>rostrum</ets> beak: cf. F.
<ets>conirostre</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A tribe of
perching birds, including those which have a strong conical bill, as the
finches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

